**Specific domain conventions for counting presents:**
- Each brother receives ONE birthday present per year, in the month of his birthday.
- Each brother receives ONE Christmas present per year (regardless of birthday month).
- Only brothers (or other specified recipients) are counted.
- First half of year: January–June; second half: July–December.
- Christmas is always in December (second half).
- When comparing halves of the year, count birthday presents according to birthday months, add Christmas presents to the second half, then calculate the difference by subtracting first half total from second half total.
- When summing presents, add only the relevant gift types for each half.

**Generalization for all problems:**
- Make all calculations explicit.
- Show every mathematical operation clearly.
- Strictly adhere to output formatting as required.

